The paper deals with security challenges faced by embedded devices in the IoT, which suggests that it belongs to the category of Computer Security and Cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also presents a hardware extension for the RISC-V core, which falls under the category of Computer Architecture (cs.AR). The use of Sponge-based authenticated encryption and control-flow integrity suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of Embedded Systems (cs.ET) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the protection of software IP and its authentic execution, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
